comments.body:
It's using native overlay for sure (there's no "mount_program" listed in the store.graphOptions), but the errors we would see when we get that wrong would show up as items which should have been deleted in a lower layer "reappearing" alongside their ".wh."-prefixed whiteouts.

 "shifting not enabled" usually means that the storage library records that the layer's set up to be used with one set of ID mappings, but it's being asked to mount them with a different set of mappings.

@HarryMichal, have the contents of the /etc/subuid or /etc/subgid files changed on your system since you started the container?  Has your UID or primary GID been changed?
